Troubleshooting File Notification Pipelines

These common issues can occur when setting up a connected app or external blob store. If you donâ€™t see data connected in your org after loading unstructured data into your external blob store and creating a file notification pipeline to Data Cloud, review these requirements.

Connected App
Ensure that you have:
Used a valid consumer key and RSA private key.
Set all three required scopes in the connected app, as documented.
Authenticated your connected app.
Uploaded a .crt file in the connected app, not a .pem or .key file.
Used a .pem file when creating the RSA private key.

Unstructured Data Files and UDLO Creation
Ensure that you have:
Correct file types were uploaded to the cloud bucket/container.

Amazon S3
Connected App
400 error in cloud function logs: The certificate (.crt) file used in the connected app is not associated with the RSA private key file (.pem) uploaded to the cloud provider.
403 error in cloud function logs: The connected app Org URL does not properly execute or is not available.
400 error in cloud function logs: The connected app policy settings are incorrect.

Data explorer
Files uploaded to the cloud bucket/container are not refreshed in UDLO/UDMO.

Google Cloud Storage
Connected App
400 error in cloud function logs: The certificate (.crt) file used in the connected app is not associated with the RSA private key file (.pem) uploaded to the cloud provider.
403 error in cloud function logs: The connected app Org URL does not properly execute or is not available.
400 error in cloud function logs: The connected app policy settings are incorrect.

Data explorer
Files uploaded to the cloud bucket/container are not refreshed in UDLO/UDMO.

GCS console
Could not deserialize the data format: The consumer key and private keys were not added properly.

GCS installer
Trigger location us-east1 not matching location us-east1.
Deployed cloud function missing: You reused a name from existing cloud function.
Can't add or set IAM policy settings for CONSUMER_KEY and RSA_PRIVATE_KEY: The necessary secret manager permission is missing from your account for the respective GCP project.
Not able to generate JWT token in cloud function logs or cloud event not reaching beacon service: You provided an invalid username, and invalid Salesforce URL, or an invalid consumer key.
Not able to generate CDP access token: The name or pattern of the secret keys does not match CONSUMER_KEY_<YOUR_OWN_SUFFIX> and RSA_PRIVATE_KEY_<YOUR_OWN_SUFFIX>.
title: Troubleshooting Salesforce Data Cloud File Notification Pipelines
